{"word":"ὄρομαι","slug":"ὄρομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75297\" key=\"o)/romai\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὄρομαι</orth>, <sense id=\"n75297.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">keep watch,</tr_> used only in compd. with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐπί,</foreign> which is always separated from the Verb by tmesis, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">αἰπόλια πλατέ) αἰγῶν . . ἐσχατιῇ βόσκοντ᾽, ἐπὶ δ᾽ ἀνέρες ἐσθλοὶ ὄρονται</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:14:104\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.104</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> ; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐπὶ δ᾽ ἀνέρες ἐσθλοὶ ὄροντο, οἶνον οἰνοχοεῦντες</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:3:471\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.471</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὄρνυμι</foreign> ad init.); <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐπὶ δ᾽ ἀνὴρ ἐσθλὸς ὀρώρει Μηριόνης</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:23:112\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.112</biblScope></bibl></cit>.—So Sch.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:14:104\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.104</biblScope> </bibl> (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅρει· φυλάσσει,</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl>) rightly : <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐπὶ . . ὄρομαι</foreign> is related to <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐπίουρος (ἔφορος᾽.</foreign> </sense> </entryFree>"}]}